Eccomi qui :) Ho trovato finalmente il testo della canzone "Weather Report
Suite I" dei Grateful Dead, e' STUPENDA la prima parte, la preferisco alla
seconda, mi piace in particolar modo quella tratta dal concerto del 19
dicembre del 1973, resa pubblica con Dick's Picks Vol. One.


Winter rain, now tell me why
Summers fade and roses die,
The answer came, the wind and rain.

Golden hills now veiled in gray
Summer leaves have blown away,
Now what remains, the wind and rain.

CHORUS:

        And like a desert spring, my lover comes
        and spreads her wings
        Knowing, like a song that's born to soar the sky
        Flowing, flowing till the waters all are dry
        Growing, the lovin'in in her eyes.

Circle song and sands of time
And seasons will end in tumbled rhyme
And little change, the wind and rain.

CHORUS

Winter gray and falling rain
We'll see summer come again
Darkness falls and seasons change
 (gonna happen ev'ry time)
Same old friends, the wind and rain
 (we'll see summer by-and-by)
Winter gray and falling rain
 (summers fade and roses die)
We'll see summer come again
 (like a song that's born to soar the sky)

